    "It was also the most popular use case for instructors in Ithaka S+R's 2024 National Instructor Survey, at 22 percent; see Dylan Ruediger, Melissa Blankstein, and Sage Love, \"Generative AI and Postsecondary Instructional Practices: Findings from a National Survey of Instructors,\" Ithaka S+R, June 20, 2024, https://doi.org/10.18665/sr.320892.",
    "For a discussion of the unreliability of LLMs like ChatGPT in academic writing in comparison to scholarly databases, see Swati Garg, Asad Ahmad, and Dag Øivind",
    "On the limitations of using AI in qualitative research, see Andrew L. Gillen, \"Can We Trust AI in Qualitative Research?\"",
